26}}, {"id": ["mesh:D009369"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "cancer", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999586343765259, "span": {"begin": 656, "end": 662}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:4780"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Nrf2", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9853124022483826, "span": {"begin": 830, "end": 834}}, {"id": ["CL:0000232"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "erythrocyte", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.8270369172096252, "span": {"begin": 885, "end": 896}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:4780"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Nrf2", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.997005045413971, "span": {"begin": 1002, "end": 1006}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:4790"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "NF-&kappa;B", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.988139808177948, "span": {"begin": 1011, "end": 1022}}, {"id": ["mesh:C565043"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "Nrf2 deficiency", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999896883964539, "span": {"begin": 1072, "end": 1087}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:4780"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Nrf2", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.871324896812439, "span": {"begin": 1072, "end": 1076}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:4780"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Nrf2", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9961496591567993, "span": {"begin": 1119, "end": 1123}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:9817"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Keap1", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9922671914100647, "span": {"begin": 1178, "end": 1183}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:4780"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Nrf2", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9794897437095642, "span": {"begin": 1206, "end": 1210}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:4780"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Nrf2", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9973413348197937, "span": {"begin": 1226, "end": 1230}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "cytoplasm", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.4730347990989685, "span": {"begin": 1303, "end": 1312}}], "text": "The presence of ROS assists in the transformation of a circulating, non-oxidized, circular-shaped beta2-glycoprotein 1 into an oxidized J-shape, which binds to antiphospholipid antibodies such as anticardiolipin, lupus anticoagulant, and anti-beta2-GP1 antibodies (Janardhan et al., 2020). Domain V of beta2gP1 binds with the phospholipid layer of platelets or endothelial cells via Annexin (Janardhan et al., 2020).  Nrf2, a basic leucine zipper transcription factor, plays a crucial role in cellular defense against oxidative stress by inducing the expression of cytoprotective and detoxifying genes.&nbsp;Activation of Nrf2 has protective roles against cancer onset and progression, while persistent activation can lead to malignant progression, chemo/radio resistance, and poor prognosis&nbsp;Pouremamali, F., et al. (2022).  Nrf2&rsquo;s involvement in inflammatory responses and erythrocyte homeostasis suggests a potential impact on blood coagulation.&nbsp;Additionally, the interaction between Nrf2 and NF-&kappa;B, and the increase in inflammatory factors due to Nrf2 deficiency, highlight the complex role of Nrf2 in cellular processes&nbsp;(Motohashi et al., 2021).  Keap1, a major regulator of Nrf2, ubiquitinates Nrf2 under basal conditions, targeting it for proteasomal degradation in the cytoplasm.&nbsp;This regulation is crucial for maintaining cellular homeostasis and responding to oxidative stress&nbsp;(Khodakarami et al., 2022).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:32:06 +0000 2026"}